1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact section 15.1-27-31.2 of the North Dakota Century Code,
2 relating to transportation weighted student unit equivalents; to amend and reenact section
3 15.1-31-05 of the North Dakota Century Code, relating to open enrollment transportation; to
4 repeal sections 15.1-27-26.1, 15.1-27-27.1, 15.1-27-28.1, 15.1-27-30.1, and 15.1-27-31.1 of the
5 North Dakota Century Code, relating to payments for school district transportation of students,
6 special education students, and career and technical education students, the distribution of
7 transportation payments in the event of school district closure, and state transportation
8 payments to school districts; and to provide an effective date.
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
10 SECTION 1. Section 15.1-27-31.2 of the North Dakota Century Code is created and
11 enacted as follows:
12 15.1 - 27 - 31.2. Transportation average daily membership equivalents converted to
13 weighted student unit equivalents - Determination .
14 1. The superintendent of public instruction shall determine transportation average daily
15 membership equivalents for eligible school districts providing schoolbus transportation
16 in contract schoolbuses, or in district-owned and operated schoolbuses, and for
17 eligible school districts with students riding commercial buses to and from a school
18 within the incorporated limits of a city. Transportation average daily membership
19 equivalents must be determined as follows:
20 a. 0.0011 multiplied by the number of eligible large bus miles;
21 b. 0.00052 multiplied by the number of eligible small bus miles;
22 c. 0.01 multiplied by the number of eligible large bus runs;
