1 d. 0.00468 multiplied by the number of eligible small bus runs;
2 e. 0.012 multiplied by the number of square miles in the school district;
3 f. 2.0 multiplied by the number of educational school plants within the school district
4 boundary; and
5 g. 0.00025 multiplied by the number of eligible miles transported by a student's
6 family and reimbursed by the school district.
7 2. The superintendent of public instruction shall determine each school district's total
8 transportation average daily membership equivalent by adding the products derived
9 under subsection 1 and then multiplying the total transportation average daily
10 membership equivalent by 0.091 to determine the school district's weighted studen t
11 unit equivalent.
12 3. Subject to legislative appropriation, the superintendent of public instruction shall pay
13 each school district providing schoolbus transportation in contract schoolbuses, or in
14 district-owned and operated schoolbuses, an amount equal to the school district's
15 weighted student unit equivalent multiplied by the per student payment rate for the
16 applicable school year in subsection 3 of section 15.1 - 27 - 04.1. For school districts
17 whose eligible bus miles and eligible bus runs remain the same, or increase from the
18 prior year, the transportation payment under this subsection may not be less than the
19 transportation payment received by the school district for the preceding year.
20 4. To be eligible, school districts must certify compliance with state law relating to
21 schoolbus standards and school vehicle driver requirements. The superintendent of
22 public instruction may adopt rules governing certification of compliance under this
23 subsection.
24 5. Each year, the superintendent of public instruction shall determine the school district's
25 transportation average daily membership equivalent based on the latest available
26 miles and runs. Eligible miles and runs include miles and runs transporting eligible
27 students to and from:
28 a. School, including miles students are transported by family transportation in
29 accordance with section 15.1 - 30 - 02 ;
30 b. Special education programs approved by the superintendent of public instruction,
31 regardless of whether the students transported live within the incorporated limits
